Namespace: dfareporting

dfareporting v2.3

DCM/DFA Reporting And Trafficking API

Manages your DoubleClick Campaign Manager ad campaigns and reports.

Version:
  • v2.3

Example

var google = require('googleapis');
var dfareporting = google.dfareporting('v2.3');

Properties
Name Type Argument Description

Allows searching for objects by name or ID. Wildcards () are allowed. For example, "account2015" will return objects with names like "account June 2015", "account April 2015", or simply "account 2015". Most of the searches also add wildcards implicitly at the start and the end of the search string. For example, a search string of "account" will match objects with name "my account", "account 2015", or simply "account".

<static> dfareporting.ads.list(params [, options], callback)

Retrieves a list of ads, possibly filtered.

Parameters:
Name Type Argument Description
params object

Parameters for request

Properties
Name Type Argument Description
active boolean <optional>

Select only active ads.
advertiserId string <optional>

Select only ads with this advertiser ID.
archived boolean <optional>

Select only archived ads.
audienceSegmentIds string <optional>

Select only ads with these audience segment IDs.
campaignIds string <optional>

Select only ads with these campaign IDs.
compatibility string <optional>

Select default ads with the specified compatibility. Applicable when type is AD_SERVING_DEFAULT_AD. WEB and WEB_INTERSTITIAL refer to rendering either on desktop or on mobile devices for regular or interstitial ads, respectively. APP and APP_INTERSTITIAL are for rendering in mobile apps. IN_STREAM_VIDEO refers to rendering an in-stream video ads developed with the VAST standard.
creativeIds string <optional>

Select only ads with these creative IDs assigned.
creativeOptimizationConfigurationIds string <optional>

Select only ads with these creative optimization configuration IDs.
creativeType string <optional>

Select only ads with the specified creativeType.
dynamicClickTracker boolean <optional>

Select only dynamic click trackers. Applicable when type is AD_SERVING_CLICK_TRACKER. If true, select dynamic click trackers. If false, select static click trackers. Leave unset to select both.
ids string <optional>

Select only ads with these IDs.
landingPageIds string <optional>

Select only ads with these landing page IDs.
maxResults integer <optional>

Maximum number of results to return.
overriddenEventTagId string <optional>

Select only ads with this event tag override ID.
pageToken string <optional>

Value of the nextPageToken from the previous result page.
placementIds string <optional>

Select only ads with these placement IDs assigned.
profileId string

User profile ID associated with this request.
remarketingListIds string <optional>

Select only ads whose list targeting expression use these remarketing list IDs.
searchString string <optional>

Allows searching for objects by name or ID. Wildcards () are allowed. For example, "ad2015" will return objects with names like "ad June 2015", "ad April 2015", or simply "ad 2015". Most of the searches also add wildcards implicitly at the start and the end of the search string. For example, a search string of "ad" will match objects with name "my ad", "ad 2015", or simply "ad".
sizeIds string <optional>

Select only ads with these size IDs.
sortField string <optional>

Field by which to sort the list.
sortOrder string <optional>

Order of sorted results, default is ASCENDING.
sslCompliant boolean <optional>

Select only ads that are SSL-compliant.
sslRequired boolean <optional>

Select only ads that require SSL.
type string <optional>

Select only ads with these types.
options object <optional>

Optionally override request options, such as url, method, and encoding.

The callback that handles the response.
